<P>
  <H1>Ramesh Jain</H1>
<P><STRONG></STRONG><P>
<P><STRONG>Director<BR> 
  <!WA0><A NAME=tex2html1 HREF="http://vision.ucsd.edu">Visual Computing Laboratory</A><BR> 
  <!WA1><A NAME=tex2html2 HREF="http://www.ucsd.edu">University of California, San Diego</A><BR> 
  9500 Gilman Drive, Mail Code 0407<BR> 
  La Jolla, CA 92093-0407</STRONG><P>
<P>
<!WA2><IMG  ALIGN=LEFT ALT="" SRC="http://vision.ucsd.edu/~jain/img1.gif">
Ramesh Jain is currently a Professor of <!WA3><A NAME=tex2html3 HREF="http://ece.ucsd.edu">Electrical and
  Computer Engineering</A>, and <!WA4><A NAME=tex2html4 HREF="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu">Computer
  Science and Engineering</A> at
<!WA5><A NAME=tex2html5 HREF="http://www.ucsd.edu">University of California, San Diego</A>.
Before joining UCSD, he was a Professor of <!WA6><A NAME=tex2html6 HREF="http://www.eecs.umich.edu">Electrical
  Engineering and Computer Science</A>, and the
founding Director of the <!WA7><A NAME=tex2html7 HREF="http://ai.eecs.umich.edu">Artificial Intelligence
  Laboratory</A> at the <!WA8><A NAME=tex2html8 HREF="http://www.umich.edu">University
  of Michigan</A>, <!WA9><A NAME=tex2html9 HREF="http://online.ann-arbor.mi.us/ann-arbor/online.html">Ann
  Arbor</A>,
<!WA10><A NAME=tex2html10 HREF="http://www.city.net/countries/united_states/michigan">MI</A>.
He has also been affiliated with <!WA11><A NAME=tex2html11 HREF="http://www.stanford.edu">Stanford
  University</A>, <!WA12><A NAME=tex2html12 HREF="http://www.almaden.ibm.com">IBM Almaden
  Research Labs</A>, General Motors Research Labs,
<!WA13><A NAME=tex2html13 HREF="http://www.wayne.edu">Wayne State University</A>,
<!WA14><A NAME=tex2html14 HREF="http://www.utexas.edu">University of Texas at Austin</A>,
<!WA15><A NAME=tex2html15 HREF="http://www.uni-hamburg.de/welcome_english.html">University of
  Hamburg</A>,
<!WA16><A NAME=tex2html16 HREF="http://www.city.net/countries/germany">Germany</A>, and
<!WA17><A NAME=tex2html17 HREF="http://www.rahul.net/kgpnet/iit/iit.html">Indian Institute of Technology,
  Kharagpur</A>,
<!WA18><A NAME=tex2html18 HREF="http://spiderman.bu.edu/misc/india">India</A>.  His current
research interests are in <!WA19><A NAME=tex2html19 HREF="http://www.virage.com/vir-res">multimedia information
  systems</A> image databases,
<!WA20><A NAME=tex2html20 HREF="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/%7Ecil/vision.html">machine
  vision</A>, and intelligent
systems.  He was the founder and the Chairman of <!WA21><A NAME=tex2html21 HREF="http://www.iware.com">Imageware
  Inc.</A>, an <!WA22><A NAME=tex2html22 HREF="http://online.ann-arbor.mi.us/ann-arbor/online.html">Ann
  Arbor</A> based company
dedicated to revolutionize software interfaces for emerging sensor
technologies.  He is the founding chairman of
<!WA23><A NAME=tex2html23 HREF="http://www.virage.com">Virage</A>, a <!WA24><A NAME=tex2html24 HREF="http://www.city.net/countries/united_states/california/san_diego">San
  Diego</A>
based company developing systems for <!WA25><A NAME=tex2html25 HREF="http://www.virage.com/vir-res">visual information
  retrieval</A>.
<P>
Ramesh is a Fellow of <!WA26><A NAME=tex2html26 HREF="http://www.ieee.org">IEEE</A>,
<!WA27><A NAME=tex2html27 HREF="http://www.aaai.org">AAAI</A>, and <!WA28><A NAME=tex2html28 HREF="http://www.spie.org">Society
  of Photo-Optical Instrumentation Engineers</A>, and
member of <!WA29><A NAME=tex2html29 HREF="http://www.acm.org">ACM</A>, Pattern Recognition
Society, Cognitive Science Society, Optical Society of America, and
<!WA30><A NAME=tex2html30 HREF="http://www.sme.org">Society of Manufacturing Engineers</A>.
He has been involved in organization of several professional conferences and
workshops, and served on editorial boards of many journals.  Currently, he is
the Editor-in-Chief of <!WA31><A NAME=tex2html31 HREF="http://www.computer.org/pubs/multimed/multimed.htm">IEEE
  Multimedia</A>, and is on
the editorial boards of Machine Vision and Applications, Pattern Recognition,
and Image and Vision Computing.  He received his Ph.D. from IIT, Kharagpur in
1975 and his B.E.  from Nagpur University in 1969.
<P>
